        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 11:42PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1141 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Eva, or 11 miles south of Elkhart. These
thunderstorms are nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eva and Sturgis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
